long_desc.thetext:
If you set the focus to a combobox using the widgetÂ´s method focus() and you try to make an input using the keyboard, you will notice that the key input will not arrive at the textfield until the second character. 
You can have a look at the following snippet to reproduce this issuse: 
------------------------------------------------------
var comboBox = new qx.ui.form.ComboBox();
for (var i=1; i<8; i++) {
  var tempItem = new qx.ui.form.ListItem("2^ " + i + " = " + Math.pow(2, i));
  comboBox.add(tempItem);
}
comboBox.addListener("changeValue", function(e) {
  this.debug("ChangeValue: " + e.getData());
});
this.getRoot().add(comboBox,
{
  left : 20,
  top  : 40
});
comboBox.focus(); 
------------------------------------------------------
BTW: You can quickly fix this problem by subclassing qx.ui.form.ComboBox and override the focus-Method like this:
------------------------------------------------------
focus: function() {
      this.base(arguments);
      var field = this.getChildControl("textfield");
      field.getFocusElement().focus();
}    
------------------------------------------------------
(This is done in the tabFocus() method, too !)
